   "source": [
    "# Model Selection & Experimentation Lab 🧬\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook allows us to **experiment with a single tile** from the dataset. It mimics the rapid, interactive learning environment of the workshop.\n",
    "By purposefully \"overfitting\" multiple model architectures on one tile, we can test their capacity to learn complex deforestation signals containing Sentinel-1 (Radar), Sentinel-2 (Optical), and AlphaEarth Foundation Embeddings.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Objectives:\n",
    "1. **Visualize** the multimodal Inputs and Ground Truth Consensus Labels.\n",
    "2. **Define** multiple model architectures (A Simple Baseline vs. an Advanced Statistical Fusion Net vs. an LSTM-based Net).\n",
    "3. **Train** them for ~50-100 steps on this single tile.\n",
    "4. **Analyze** their predictions to select the best architecture for `train.py`."
   ]
  },
